.TH "TREEX" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
treex \- enhanced directory tree with colour, filtering, and size
rollups
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]treex\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]paths\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Walks one or more directories (default: \f[B].\f[R] ) and renders a
tree\-formatted listing to stdout.
Supports glob and regex filtering, size rollups, date display, sort
order, gitignore, and clickable terminal hyperlinks.
.PP
A cross\-platform \f[B]tree\f[R] replacement with full ANSI colour and
filtering capabilities.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-g\f[R], \f[B]\(englob\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R]
Match filenames against a glob pattern (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-e\f[R], \f[B]\(enregex\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R]
Match filenames against a regex (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\(enext\f[R] \f[I]EXT\f[R]
Match file extension, e.g.\ \f[B]cs\f[R], \f[B]log\f[R] (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entype\f[R] \f[I]TYPE\f[R]
Filter by type: \f[B]f\f[R] (file), \f[B]d\f[R] (directory), \f[B]l\f[R]
(symlink).
.TP
\f[B]\(enmin\-size\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
Minimum file size (e.g.\ \f[B]100k\f[R], \f[B]10M\f[R], \f[B]1G\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enmax\-size\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
Maximum file size (e.g.\ \f[B]100k\f[R], \f[B]10M\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(ennewer\f[R] \f[I]DURATION\f[R]
Modified within \f[I]DURATION\f[R] (e.g.\ \f[B]1h\f[R], \f[B]30m\f[R],
\f[B]7d\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enolder\f[R] \f[I]DURATION\f[R]
Not modified within \f[I]DURATION\f[R] (e.g.\ \f[B]1h\f[R],
\f[B]7d\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(enmax\-depth\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Maximum directory depth (0 = root only).
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-hidden\f[R]
Skip hidden files and directories.
.TP
\f[B]\(engitignore\f[R]
Respect \f[B].gitignore\f[R] rules.
.TP
\f[B]\-i\f[R], \f[B]\(enignore\-case\f[R]
Case\-insensitive name matching.
.TP
\f[B]\(encase\-sensitive\f[R]
Case\-sensitive name matching.
.TP
\f[B]\-s\f[R], \f[B]\(ensize\f[R]
Show file sizes.
.TP
\f[B]\(endate\f[R]
Show last\-modified dates.
.TP
\f[B]\(ensort\f[R] \f[I]MODE\f[R]
Sort order: \f[B]name\f[R] (default), \f[B]size\f[R],
\f[B]modified\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-D\f[R], \f[B]\(endirs\-only\f[R]
Show only directories.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-links\f[R]
Disable clickable terminal hyperlinks.
.TP
\f[B]\(enndjson\f[R]
Streaming NDJSON to stdout, one JSON object per node.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\f[R]
JSON summary to stderr on exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(endescribe\f[R]
Print machine\-readable metadata and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(encolor\f[R]
Force coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-color\f[R]
Disable coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
Show version.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
Show help.
.SH SIZE UNITS
\f[B]\(enmin\-size\f[R] and \f[B]\(enmax\-size\f[R] accept an optional
unit suffix: \f[B]b\f[R] (bytes), \f[B]k\f[R] (1024 bytes), \f[B]M\f[R]
(megabytes), \f[B]G\f[R] (gigabytes).
No suffix means bytes.
.SH DURATION UNITS
\f[B]\(ennewer\f[R] and \f[B]\(enolder\f[R] accept a number followed by
a unit: \f[B]s\f[R] (seconds), \f[B]m\f[R] (minutes), \f[B]h\f[R]
(hours), \f[B]d\f[R] (days), \f[B]w\f[R] (weeks).
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Runtime error (permission denied, invalid path).
.TP
\f[B]125\f[R]
Usage error (bad arguments).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]NO_COLOR\f[R]
If set, disables coloured output.
Clickable hyperlinks are also disabled when colour is off
(no\-color.org).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
treex

treex src \-\-ext cs

treex \-\-size \-\-gitignore \-\-no\-hidden

treex \-\-size \-\-sort size

treex \-d 2

treex src tests

treex \-\-ndjson | jq \(aq.name\(aq
.EE
